After reviewing the available contracts, the agent decides whether to accept one. If he does not accept any contract, both parties make their reservation level of profits, which are assumed to be zero. If a contract is accepted, then the agent generates the appropriate level of unit sales or selects the appropriate price in order to maximize his profit, given the specific monitoring system in place and the particular contract that is agreed upon.8

